This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new transfer learning method for training neural networks. It also involves fine-tuning and random initialization, which are common techniques in machine learning. 

It is also likely to belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the experiments are conducted on image datasets and the proposed method is evaluated based on image classification performance. 

Furthermore, it could belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as the paper discusses the vulnerability of fine-tuning to adversarial attacks and proposes a method to improve the robustness of transfer learning. 

It may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves training neural networks and improving their performance. 

Finally, it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it proposes a new method for training neural networks and evaluates its performance.
